+## API Mocking
+
+Tests use the `api-mocks.ts` helper to mock API responses. This approach:
+- **Eliminates backend dependency** - Tests run independently
+- **Improves test speed** - No network latency
+- **Increases reliability** - No external service failures
+- **Simplifies CI/CD** - No need to spin up backend services
+
+### Using Mocks in Tests
+
+```typescript
+import { mockCommonEndpoints } from './helpers/api-mocks';
+
+test('my test', async ({ page }) => {
+  // Mock all common API endpoints
+  await mockCommonEndpoints(page);
+  
+  await page.goto('/knowledge');
+  // ... test assertions
+});
+```
+
+### Available Mock Functions
+
+- `mockEmptyKnowledgeBases(page)` - Returns empty knowledge list
+- `mockKnowledgeBases(page, data?)` - Returns sample knowledge bases
+- `mockOllamaModels(page, models?)` - Returns sample Ollama models
+- `mockAnalyticsEndpoints(page)` - Mocks all analytics endpoints
+- `mockCommonEndpoints(page)` - Mocks all common endpoints at once
+
